In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jay Carney discussed a range of topics including the VA scandal, the Ukraine crisis, and the extension of unemployment benefits. He expressed concern about the House Appropriations Committee's proposal to undercut school nutrition standards and mentioned that the President is troubled by the preliminary report from the Inspector General on the VA scandal. Carney also mentioned that the President believes in accountability and expects to receive a preliminary report from Secretary Shinseki on the VA scandal by the end of the week. He emphasized the importance of taking action to improve care and services for veterans while the investigations are ongoing. Carney also addressed questions about the President's confidence in Secretary Shinseki, but did not provide a direct answer.